article.headline: South Carolina 72, South Florida 70
article.story: COLUMBIA, S.C. (AP) -- Renaldo Balkman scored a career-high 17 points and South Carolina rallied for a 72-70 victory over South Florida on Tuesday night. Terrence Leather had 24 points for South Florida, which had two chances to tie or take the lead in the final seconds. Leather's three-point play with 28 seconds to go brought the Bulls (5-4) within 71-70. Carlos Powell than made one of two free throws to put the Gamecocks (5-1) up 72-70. South Florida's Brian Swift drove the lane only to have Brandon Wallace block the shot into the stands with 4.1 seconds to go. Swift launched a 3-pointer from the corner over a leaping Rocky Trice with about a second left, but the ball bounced off the rim toward halfcourt. South Florida scored the first six points of the second half to go up 51-43 with 14:30 left. Leather sandwiched a three-point play and a fastbreak layup around Marius Prekevicius's 3-pointer. But South Carolina countered with a 17-4 run in which Balkman had seven points and Antoine Tisby had the go-ahead basket with 7:58 left and a short jumper that capped the run and gave the Gamecocks a 60-55 lead with 6:31 to go.
